The Indian Space Research Organization (ISRO) and the French National Space Center have signed an agreement to initiate a satellite project which will gather atmospheric data.
India will build the satellite and France the scientific instruments.
ISRO is also considering scientific experiments from the US, UK, Sweden, Bulgaria and Germany for an unmanned lunar mission.
India hopes to launch a manned mission within seven years.
ISRO is assisting the Jharkhand Space Application Center launch a telemedicine satellite system to connect doctors with rural communities.
Afghanistan is requesting to piggyback on the telemedicine system to assist their citizens.
